# For each line of input, output the number with the largest value when read from right to left
# The numbers are guaranteed to be non-zero, three-digit numbers

# Read in the numbers
a, b = input().split()

# Reverse the numbers and convert them to integers
a, b = int(a[::-1]), int(b[::-1])

# Print the larger number
print(max(a, b))
